var x = 1;
var x = 2;            Var does NOT provide error when you overwrite it
const y = 3;          constant value

//global scope

var x = 4;
let y = 5;
const z = 6;    At this point all of them are GLOBAL now

// local scope - variable are not available in global scope

{
    let y = 7;
}  - BLOCK scope

function myFunc() = {
    const z = 8;
}   - function scope

When we call function inside global scope then it will revive variables inside function scope

If inside the function theres block scope then function will use global scope

var instances function() scoped variables
let and const instantiate {block} scoped variables

AVOID using var